data.name: ConnHelp
data.value:
1) Connect the headset to your computer 2) Set the switch to "AirLink (or VD)". 3) Wait for ADB to switch to TCPIP mode. 4) Click the "Start by Default" button to connect.
If this does not work Connecting manually Enter "platform-tools\adb tcpip 5555" "platform-tools\\\\adb connect QUEST_IP:5555."

data.name: ExitNote
data.value: Do you want to log out? Note that this action will stop the ADB server

data.name: LocalHostErr
data.value: This function cannot be activated if HostIP is not equal to 127.0.0.1

data.name: NewOrOld
data.value: Do you want the program to find the IP address the old way or with ZeroConf? Searching via ZeroConf requires an additional program to be installed on Quest "https://github.com/Sergey004/Quest2-VRC/releases/tag/Addon". Yes for ZeroConf, No for the old method

data.name: WakeDevice
data.value: Remember to wake up your device
